Install mongodb on system

then run database =>

	create folder for database then move into, create sub folder data for example, then 
		 mongod --dbpath=data
	will create database in data and serve database on port 27017

cd into app, then run load the db with

	node loaddb

press control + c to return to terminal after brief wait

Install dependencies

	npm install

move into app folder and run app

	npm start

go to web browser and go to localhost:3000

CAVEOTS
	database url inside app.js on backend must be correct, should not be issue though.
	If port 3000 is in use listen on alternative port
